            <thetext>If a developer does use an e.g. HBox decorator with a baseImage which is currently not available the &quot;qx.ui.decoration.css3.BorderImage&quot; class does throw an error like

     &#39;Error in property sliceRight of class qx.ui.decoration.css3.BorderImage in method setSliceRight with incoming value &#39;null&#39;: Null value is not allowed!&#39;
     
This error message is not very helpful, since the resource which is missing is not mentioned. To be able to debug this effectively the framework should provide the resource name of the image which is missing.</thetext>
